      <description>&lt;h4 id=&#34;the-new-republic-long-form-features&#34;&gt;THE NEW REPUBLIC (long form features)&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://newrepublic.com/article/201121/france-royal-wolf-catchers-kill&#34;&gt;When is it right to kill a wolf?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://newrepublic.com/article/208944/polish-ukrainian-honeymoon&#34;&gt;The Polish-Ukrainian Honeymoon Is Over&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;scientific-american&#34;&gt;SCIENTIFIC AMERICAN&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/you-can-literally-sniff-out-other-peoples-inner-feelings/&#34;&gt;You Can Literally Sniff Out Other People&amp;rsquo;s Inner Feelings&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/hear-the-violet-taste-the-velvet/&#34;&gt;Hear the Violet, Taste the Velvet&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/with-age-comes-happiness-here-s-why/&#34;&gt;With Age Comes Happiness: Here&amp;rsquo;s Why&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/with-age-comes-happiness-here-s-why/&#34;&gt;How Global Warming Is Shrinking Earth&amp;rsquo;s Animals&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/hear-the-violet-taste-the-velvet/&#34;&gt;Meet the Meat Paradox&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/food-can-be-literally-addictive-new-evidence-suggests/&#34;&gt;Food Can Be Literally Addictive&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.scientificamerican.com/author/marta-zaraska/&#34;&gt;and more&amp;hellip;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;the-new-york-times&#34;&gt;THE NEW YORK TIMES&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.nytimes.com/2024/09/13/climate/dirty-birds-color-climate-pollution.html&#34;&gt;The Big City Is Vibrant. Birds There Might Be Getting Less So.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.nytimes.com/2024/06/18/well/mind/nose-mental-health-brain-smell.html&#34;&gt;The Surprising Link Between Your Sense of Smell and Brain Health&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;the-atlantic&#34;&gt;THE ATLANTIC&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2013/08/is-lab-grown-meat-good-for-us/278778&#34;&gt;Will lab-grown meat be healthier than conventional meat?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.theatlantic.com/science/archive/2023/09/building-birdhouse-artificial-shelters-climate-change/675350/&#34;&gt;The Quest to Build a Better Birdhouse&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.theatlantic.com/science/archive/2023/02/fight-against-mosquitoes-now-high-tech/673125/&#34;&gt;The Next Generation of Mosquito Factories&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.theatlantic.com/science/archive/2016/02/when-humans-became-meateaters/463305/&#34;&gt;How Humans Became Meat Eaters&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;the-washington-post&#34;&gt;THE WASHINGTON POST&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.washingtonpost.com/science/upcycling-food-waste/2021/09/17/90fd81b2-0045-11ec-85f2-b871803f65e4_story.html&#34;&gt;Loneliness can be depressing, but it may have helped us survive&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.washingtonpost.com/science/upcycling-food-waste/2021/09/17/90fd81b2-0045-11ec-85f2-b871803f65e4_story.html&#34;&gt;Upcycling food waste onto our plates is a new effort. But will consumers find it appetizing?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/health-science/what-makes-a-hamburger-and-other-cooked-meat-so-enticing-to-humans/2013/08/12/8f8e1d72-ff73-11e2-9711-3708310f6f4d_story.html?itid=sr_14&#34;&gt;What makes a hamburger and other cooked meat so enticing to humans?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.washingtonpost.com/national/health-science/your-kid-hates-veggies-you-may-be-to-blame-but-its-possible-to-make-peas-more-palatable/2014/03/17/ac9e39d8-8466-11e3-9dd4-e7278db80d86_story.html&#34;&gt;Your kid hates veggies? You may be to blame&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.washingtonpost.com/national/health-science/too-much-happiness-can-make-you-unhappy-studies-show/2012/04/02/gIQACELLrS_story.html&#34;&gt;Baby boomers embrace vegetarianism&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.washingtonpost.com/wellness/2023/05/23/vegetables-fruit-mental-health/&#34;&gt;Want to improve your mental health? Eat your greens&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.washingtonpost.com/national/health-science/too-much-happiness-can-make-you-unhappy-studies-show/2012/04/02/gIQACELLrS_story.html&#34;&gt;Too much happiness can make you unhappy, studies show&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.washingtonpost.com/national/health-science/too-much-happiness-can-make-you-unhappy-studies-show/2012/04/02/gIQACELLrS_story.html&#34;&gt;Vacations don&amp;rsquo;t keep people satisfied for long once they return home&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;and more&amp;hellip;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;bbc&#34;&gt;BBC&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Why being kind to others is good for your health&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.bbc.com/future/article/20230118-how-to-make-fruit-and-vegetables-last-longer&#34;&gt;How to make fruit and vegetables last longer&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;The tomatoes at the forefront of a food revolution&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;quanta-magazine&#34;&gt;QUANTA MAGAZINE&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.quantamagazine.org/how-loneliness-reshapes-the-brain-20230228/&#34;&gt;How Loneliness Reshapes the Brain&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.quantamagazine.org/the-social-benefits-of-getting-our-brains-in-sync-20240328/&#34;&gt;The Social Benefits of Getting Our Brains in Sync&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;discover&#34;&gt;DISCOVER&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.discovermagazine.com/planet-earth/non-mammals-like-to-play-too&#34;&gt;Raising the steaks: How one city in the Netherlands wants to feed the world&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.discovermagazine.com/planet-earth/non-mammals-like-to-play-too&#34;&gt;Non-mammals Like to Play, Too&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.discovermagazine.com/planet-earth/garden-greenery-is-brainier-than-you-think&#34;&gt;Garden Greenery is Brainier Than You Think&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;and more&amp;hellip;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;mother-jones&#34;&gt;MOTHER JONES&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.motherjones.com/environment/2017/01/yeast-animal-free-milk-perfect-day-cow-synthetic-biology/&#34;&gt;Your Breakfast Is About to Take a Weird Turn&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;medscape&#34;&gt;MEDSCAPE&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.medscape.com/viewarticle/964437&#34;&gt;MDMA Therapy for Loneliness? Researchers Say It Could Work&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.webmd.com/mental-health/news/20240408/saying-hello-stranger-could-be-key-to-better-health&#34;&gt;Why Saying &amp;lsquo;Hello, Stranger&amp;rsquo; Could Be Key to Better Health&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.medscape.com/viewarticle/992776&#34;&gt;Unlocking the Riddle of REM Sleep&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.medscape.com/viewarticle/981201?form=fpf&#34;&gt;Limiting Antibiotic Overprescription in Pandemics&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.medscape.com/viewarticle/975668&#34;&gt;Ancient Human Teeth Revise the History of Microbial Evolution&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;and more&amp;hellip;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;new-scientist&#34;&gt;NEW SCIENTIST&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg23331180-400-tomorrows-menu-termites-grass-and-synthetic-milk/&#34;&gt;Tomorrow&amp;rsquo;s menu: Termites, grass and synthetic milk&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg23731650-200-dirty-talk-how-pollution-is-snuffing-out-plants-scent-messages/&#34;&gt;Dirty talk: How pollution is snuffing out plants&amp;rsquo; scent messages&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.newscientist.com/article/mg22730322-100-bitter-truth-how-were-making-fruit-and-veg-less-healthy/&#34;&gt;Bitter truth: How we&amp;rsquo;re making fruit and veg less healthy&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;the-guardian-long-reads&#34;&gt;THE GUARDIAN LONG READS&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2025/jun/19/world-worst-case-of-pfas-forever-chemicals-contamination-kallinge&#34;&gt;Poison in the water: the town with the world&amp;rsquo;s worst case of forever chemicals contamination&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.theguardian.com/news/2026/may/12/i-couldnt-breathe-the-sinister-spread-of-frances-killer-seaweed&#34;&gt;&amp;lsquo;I couldn&amp;rsquo;t breathe&amp;rsquo;: the sinister spread of France&amp;rsquo;s killer seaweed&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;breakthrough&#34;&gt;BREAKTHROUGH&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://thebreakthrough.org/journal/no-12-winter-2020/kind-to-the-climate&#34;&gt;Must We Be Cruel to Be Kind to the Climate?&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://thebreakthrough.org/journal/no-10-winter-2019/meeting-meat-eaters-halfway&#34;&gt;Meeting Meat-Eaters Halfway&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;vox&#34;&gt;VOX&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.vox.com/future-perfect/22360062/meat-vegetarian-vegan-lyon-france-culture-identity&#34;&gt;A French city announced it would serve meatless school lunches. The backlash was swift&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h6 id=&#34;newspapers-and-magazines-for-which-i-have-written-in-the-past&#34;&gt;NEWSPAPERS AND MAGAZINES FOR WHICH I HAVE WRITTEN IN THE PAST:&lt;/h6&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;WASHINGTON POST, GLOBE &amp;amp; MAIL, BOSTON GLOBE, THE LOS ANGELES TIMES, NEW INTERNATIONALIST, NEWSWEEK, NATIONAL GEOGRAPHIC, ELLE, POLITYKA, FOCUS, COACHING, SCIENTIFIC AMERICAN, NEW SCIENTIST, THE ATLANTIC, OPEN SKIES, HIGH LIFE MAGAZINE, SILVERKRIS, TWÓJ STYL, GAZETA WYBORCZA, DZIECKO, PREGNANCY &amp;amp; NEWBORN, &amp;hellip;AND MANY OTHERS&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Books</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/books/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/books/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div class=&#34;book-entry&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;book-top&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/img/growing_young_cover.avif&#34; alt=&#34;Growing Young book cover&#34; class=&#34;book-cover-main&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;book-info&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2&gt;GROWING YOUNG:&lt;br&gt;How Friendship, Optimism and Kindness Can Help You Live to 100&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;June 2020, Penguin Random House/Little, Brown&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A Globe and Mail bestseller&#xA;Bestseller, South Korea&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;If you care about the length and quality of your life but can&amp;rsquo;t stomach yet another diet or workout routine, this book is for you.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;—Adam Grant, author &amp;ldquo;Give and Take&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Finally, a lifestyle book that transcends diet and exercise as solutions for living longer. This well-researched book shows us the subtle power of community and connection as tools for a quest to live to 100.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
